#: ../../introduction/screenshots.rst:32 62dba906ac654f879928a3a19b4e82f2
msgid ""
"Qubes Release 2 can also run Windows AppVMs in seamless mode, integrated "
"onto the common Qubes trusted desktop, just like Linux AppVMs! The "
"seamless GUI integration has been introduced in Qubes R2 Beta 3. This "
"requires :doc:`Qubes Windows Tools </user/templates/windows/qubes-"
"windows-tools>` to be installed in the Windows VMs first."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/screenshots.rst:38 2ebe33840b1648a79a13e420f69a68c4
msgid "|r2b3-windows-seamless-filecopy.png|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/screenshots.rst:136 b05562280a37495ebe2071a9eb30b2e7
msgid "r2b3-windows-seamless-filecopy.png"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/screenshots.rst:40 f3c9151acfd74e5a8b2ccb1dd948c69f
msgid ""
"Windows AppVMs are fully integrated with the rest of the Qubes OS system,"
" which includes things such as secure, policy governed, inter-VM file "
"copy, clipboard, and generally our whole elastic qrexec infrastructure "
"for secure inter-VM RPC! Starting with Qubes R2 Beta 3 we also support "
"HVM-based templates allowing to instantly create many Windows AppVMs with"
" shared “root filesystem” from the Template VM (but one should ensure "
"their license allows for such instantiation of the OS in the template). "
"Just like with Linux AppVMs!"
msgstr ""

