#: ../../introduction/screenshots.rst:64 1edad7013b4c4a3b9e87003d59cb4d70
msgid ""
"Qubes is all about seamless integration from the user’s point of view. "
"Here you can see how it virtualizes tray icons from other domains. Notice"
" the network icon is in red. This icon is in fact managed by the Network "
"Manager running in a separate NetVM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/screenshots.rst:70 8bb39532801c4062a30a8e12bab8e6e7
msgid "|r4.0-manager-and-sysnet-network-prompt.png|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/screenshots.rst:140 c4c4cc8d866747bf96fda006be09cb69
msgid "r4.0-manager-and-sysnet-network-prompt.png"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/screenshots.rst:72 4a42aec91e204bcf9b18b908209408e6
msgid ""
"All the networking runs in a special, unprivileged NetVM. (Notice the red"
" frame around the Network Manager dialog box on the screen above.) This "
"means that in the event that your network card driver, Wi-Fi stack, or "
"DHCP client is compromised, the integrity of the rest of the system will "
"not be affected! This feature requires Intel VT-d or AMD IOMMU hardware "
"(e.g., Core i5/i7 systems)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/screenshots.rst:78 0415de31c7f04567979e4ba5d995c906
msgid "|r4.0-software-update.png|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/screenshots.rst:141 b66ac51975b84d2c833949b1cf01657b
msgid "r4.0-software-update.png"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/screenshots.rst:80 6157abad980849a2934c31f240ecca42
msgid ""
"Qubes lets you update all the software in all the domains all at once, in"
" a centralized way. This is possible thanks to Qubes’ unique TemplateVM "
"technology. Note that the user is not required to shut down any AppVMs "
"(domains) for the update process. This can be done later, at a convenient"
" moment, and separately for each AppVM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/screenshots.rst:86 0cfbfdfcfd864f94b0d5e44d6104981d
